Definition 1.1 (Altenkirch, Chapman and Uustalu). A relative monad on a functor $I:\mathbb{C}_{0}\rightarrow\mathbb{C}$ consists of: • an object mapping $S\colon\textrm{Ob}(\mathbb{C})\to\textrm{Ob}(\mathbb{C})$; • for any $x,\,y\in\mathbb{C}_{0}$, a map $(-)^{\ast}_{S}:\mathbb{C}(Ix,\,Sy)\rightarrow\mathbb{C}(Sx,\,Sy)$ (the extension); • for any $x\in\mathbb{C}_{0}$, a map $s_{x}:Ix\rightarrow Sx$ (the unit); satisfying the following axioms • the left unital law, i.e. for any $k\colon Ix\to Sy$, $k=k^{\ast}\cdot s_{x}$; • the right unital law, i.e. for any $x\in\mathbb{C}_{0}$, $s_{x}^{\ast}=Id_{Sx}$; • the associativity law, i.e. for any $k:Ix\rightarrow Sy$ and $l:Iy\rightarrow Sz$, $(l^{\ast}\cdot k)^{\ast}=l^{\ast}\cdot k^{\ast}$.
