Definition 5.1. Let $I\colon X_{0}\rightarrow X$ be 1-cell in a 2-category $\mathcal{K}$. A monad compatible with $I$ consists of a pair of monads $(X_{0},\,S_{0})$ and $(X,\,S)$ in $\mathcal{K}$ such that $SI=IS_{0}$, $mI=Im_{0}$ and $sI=Is_{0}$. We will denote it with $(S,\,S_{0})$.
